    "long_instructions": "#Do This:\r\n\r\n#\r\n1. Run the code and observe. \r\n#\r\n2. *Discuss:*\r\n\t- The painter passed over a paint bucket. What do you think it's purpose is? \r\n#\r\n3. Uncomment (delete the #'s) the code on lines 11-14, 18, 20, and 22. Then run the program. \r\n#\r\n4. *Discuss:* \r\n\t- Was your prediction about the bucket accurate?\r\n    - What does the number on the bucket represent? \r\n#\r\n5. Paint a yellow line to the cone. \r\n\t- See the documentation for how to change the color of the paint.",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nzoe = Painter()\n\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.move()\n\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")",
